  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nIt seems the Send modal is not handling background balance updates correctly. If left open for some time after entering an amount and a recipient address, it will eventually show \"No Balances Active\".\r\n\r\n![Screenshot 2023-02-06 at 11 01 09 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11161531/216992854-fc546007-55f4-4b99-a65c-279d24a88d2a.png)\r\n\r\n![Screenshot 2023-02-06 at 11 07 09 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11161531/216992878-63dfbfea-b388-4896-af06-4b39f76e4e99.png)\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open the Wallet's Send modal.\r\n2. Enter a valid recipient address and amount. You should get proper fees calculation\r\n3. Wait for a couple of minutes on that state. Eventually, the \"No balances active\" error message will be shown.\r\n",
